{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2013}} {{Infobox person | name = Shahram Jalilian | image =Dr Shahram Jalilian.jpg | alt = 250px | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1978|05|08}} | birth_place = [[Khorramshahr]], Iran | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} or {{Death-date and age|df=yes|Month DD, YYYY|Month DD, YYYY}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | nationality = [[Demographics of Iran|Iran]]ian | other_names = | occupation = [[Iranology|Iranologist]], writer, translator and [[Faculty (academic staff)|academic staff]] | known_for = | website ={{Official website|http://www.shahramjalilian.com}} }} '''Shahram Jalilian''' ({{Lang-fa|شهرام جلیلیان}}) (born 1978 in [[Khorramshahr]], [[Iran]]) is an [[Iranian people|Iranian]] [[Iranology|Iranologist]] and historian. his Higher education was in [[Shahid Beheshti University]] and took his doctorate in History of Ancient Iran at the [[University of Tehran]]. He is now the [[Associate Professor]] in the history of Ancient Iran at [[Shahid Chamran University of Ahvaz]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scu.ac.ir/HomePage.aspx?site=lite.scu.ac&tabid=4900&lang=fa-IR|title=Shahram Jalilian|publisher=[[Shahid Chamran University of Ahvaz]]|language=fa|accessdate=27 November 2013}}</ref>
